<tmc-service-paragraph><pub id="RM25T0E"><servcat id="_53"><name>Suspension</name><section id="_062777"><name>TIRE PRESSURE MONITORING</name><ttl id="_0306275"><name>TIRE PRESSURE WARNING SYSTEM</name><para id="RM1000000012NTR" category="J"><dtccode/><dtcname>Tire Pressure Warning Light Circuit</dtcname><subpara id="RM1000000012NTR_02" category="03"><name>DESCRIPTION</name><content5><ptxt>If the tire pressure warning ECU and receiver detects a disconnected connector or an open circuit between the tire pressure warning ECU and receiver and combination meter assembly, the tire pressure warning light blinks for 1 minute, and then remains on after the ignition switch is turned to on.</ptxt></content5></subpara><subpara id="RM1000000012NTR_03" category="03"><name>WIRING DIAGRAM</name><content5><figure type="1" translate="E"><graphic graphicname="C171956E22" width="7.168479331in" height="2.799876969in"/></figure></content5></subpara><subpara id="RM1000000012NTR_04" category="10"><name>CAUTION / NOTICE / HINT</name><content5><atten3><list1 type="unordered"><item><ptxt>When replacing the tire pressure warning ECU and receiver, read the transmitter IDs stored in the old ECU using the GTS and write them down before removal.</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>It is necessary to perform initialization <mlink><xref label="Seep00001" term-id-from="003" href="RM1000000012NUB"/></mlink> after registration <mlink><xref label="Seep00002" term-id-from="003" href="RM1000000012NUA"/></mlink> of the transmitter IDs into the tire pressure warning ECU and receiver if the ECU has been replaced.</ptxt></item></list1></atten3></content5></subpara><subpara id="RM1000000012NTR_05" category="01"><name>PROCEDURE</name><testgrp id="RM1000000012NTR_05_0003" cellposition="1-1"><testtitle>CHECK HARNESS AND CONNECTOR (COMBINATION METER ASSEMBLY - TIRE PRESSURE WARNING ECU AND RECEIVER)</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Turn the ignition switch off.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Disconnect the S30*1, Y7*2 or U5*3 tire pressure warning ECU and receiver connector.</ptxt><list1 type="nonmark"><item><ptxt>*1: for Single Cab</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>*2: for Double Cab</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>*3: except Single and Double Cabs</ptxt></item></list1></test1><test1><ptxt>Disconnect the L25 combination meter assembly connector.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Measure the resistance according to the value(s) in the table below.</ptxt><spec type="resistance"><title>Standard Resistance</title><table><tgroup cols="3"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.37in"/><thead><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Condition</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Specified Condition</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>S30-5 (IND) - L25-5 (TIRE)*1</ptxt><ptxt>Y7-5 (IND) - L25-5 (TIRE)*2</ptxt><ptxt>U5-5 (IND) - L25-5 (TIRE)*3</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle" align="center"><ptxt>Below 1 Ω</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>S30-5 (IND) or L25-5 (TIRE) - Body ground*1</ptxt><ptxt>Y7-5 (IND) or L25-5 (TIRE) - Body ground*2</ptxt><ptxt>U5-5 (IND) or L25-5 (TIRE) - Body ground*3</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Always</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>10 kΩ or higher</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec><list1 type="nonmark"><item><ptxt>*1: for Single Cab</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>*2: for Double Cab</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>*3: except Single and Double Cabs</ptxt></item></list1></test1><spec type="other"><title>Result</title><table><tgroup cols="1"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="4.13in"/><thead><row><entry align="center"><ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="center"><judge-value label="1"><ptxt>OK</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row><row><entry align="center"><judge-value label="2"><ptxt>NG</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></content6><results><result label="1" cellposition="1-1"><action actiontype="next" cellposition="3-1" childid="RM1000000012NTR_05_0006"/></result><result label="2" cellposition="1-2"><action actiontype="end" cellposition="2-2"><actiontitle>REPAIR OR REPLACE HARNESS OR CONNECTOR</actiontitle><content6/></action></result></results></testgrp><testgrp id="RM1000000012NTR_05_0006" cellposition="3-1"><testtitle>CHECK OPERATION OF TIRE PRESSURE WARNING LIGHT (ACTIVE TEST)</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Turn the ignition switch off.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Connect the GTS to the DLC3.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Turn the ignition switch to ON.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Turn the GTS on.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Enter the following menus: Body Electrical / Combination Meter / Active Test.</ptxt></test1><test1><ptxt>Check the condition of the tire pressure warning light by using the GTS.</ptxt><gts-info category="active-test-table"><title>Body Electrical &gt; Combination Meter &gt; Active Test</title><table pgwide="1" type="active-test-table"><tgroup cols="4"><colspec colname="1" colwidth="1.77in"/><colspec colname="2" colwidth="1.77in"/><colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.77in"/><colspec colname="4" colwidth="1.77in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Tester Display</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Measurement Item</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Control Range</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Diagnostic Note</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="item-name" args1="57"><ptxt>Indicat. Tire Pressure Warning System</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="description" args1="57"><ptxt>Tire pressure warning light</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><data-name name="drive-range" args1="57"><ptxt>OFF or ON</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="remark" args1="57"><ptxt>Confirm that the vehicle is stopped with the engine idling.</ptxt></data-name></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><app-communication><app-param name="process-mode">0</app-param><app-param name="edit-mode">1</app-param><app-param name="insert-mode">1</app-param><app-param name="function-tab">3</app-param><app-param name="category-div">3</app-param><app-param name="category-div-name">Body Electrical</app-param><app-param name="ecu-id">122</app-param><app-param name="ecu-name">Combination Meter</app-param><app-param name="gts-order">1</app-param><app-param-unit><app-param name="did-id">57</app-param><app-param name="active-test-item-name">Indicat. Tire Pressure Warning System</app-param><app-param name="exception-process-id"/><app-param name="exception-process-div"/></app-param-unit></app-communication></gts-info><gts-info category="active-test"><title>Body Electrical &gt; Combination Meter &gt; Active Test</title><table type="active-test"><tgroup cols="1"><colspec colname="1" colwidth="4.13in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Tester Display</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="item-name" args1="57"><ptxt>Indicat. Tire Pressure Warning System</ptxt></data-name></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><gts-exec function-id="50004"><gts-ecu ecu-id="122"><gts-did did-id="57"/></gts-ecu></gts-exec><app-communication><app-param name="process-mode">0</app-param><app-param name="edit-mode">1</app-param><app-param name="insert-mode">0</app-param><app-param name="function-tab">3</app-param><app-param name="category-div">3</app-param><app-param name="category-div-name">Body Electrical</app-param><app-param name="ecu-id">122</app-param><app-param name="ecu-name">Combination Meter</app-param><app-param name="gts-order">0</app-param><app-param name="use-datalist">0</app-param><app-param-unit><app-param name="did-id">57</app-param><app-param name="active-test-item-name">Indicat. Tire Pressure Warning System</app-param><app-param name="exception-process-id"/><app-param name="exception-process-div"/></app-param-unit></app-communication></gts-info><spec type="other"><title>OK</title><specitem><ptxt>The tire pressure warning light turns on or off in accordance with the GTS operation.</ptxt></specitem></spec><spec type="other"><title>Result</title><table><tgroup cols="1"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="4.13in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><judge-value label="1"><ptxt>OK</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><judge-value label="2"><ptxt>NG</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></test1></content6><results><result label="1" cellposition="3-1"><action actiontype="end" cellposition="4-1"><actiontitle>REPLACE TIRE PRESSURE WARNING ECU AND RECEIVER</actiontitle><content6><ptxt>for Single Cab: Click here<mlink><xref label="Seep00001" term-id-from="003" href="RM1000000013GKS"/></mlink></ptxt><ptxt>for Double Cab: Click here<mlink><xref label="Seep00002" term-id-from="003" href="RM1000000013GKS"/></mlink></ptxt><ptxt>for Short Body: Click here<mlink><xref label="Seep00003" term-id-from="003" href="RM1000000013GKK"/></mlink></ptxt><ptxt>for Long Body: Click here<mlink><xref label="Seep00004" term-id-from="003" href="RM1000000013GKW"/></mlink></ptxt><ptxt>for Semi-long Body: Click here<mlink><xref label="Seep00005" term-id-from="003" href="RM1000000013GKZ"/></mlink></ptxt></content6></action></result><result label="2" cellposition="3-2"><action actiontype="end" cellposition="4-2"><actiontitle>GO TO METER / GAUGE SYSTEM</actiontitle><content6><ptxt>Click here<mlink><xref label="Seep00001" term-id-from="003" href="RM1000000013L9N"/></mlink></ptxt></content6></action></result></results></testgrp></subpara></para></ttl></section></servcat></pub></tmc-service-paragraph>